  <title>Oxfam : Improved productivity for smallholder farmers</title>
  <description>The project will support the small livestock women and men farmers to form producer groups and collectively increase the livestock productivity through establishing a system of veterinary services including trained and equipped livestock extension workers. The project will mainly focus on increasing the incomes of the target beneficiaries through increased food production capacities and capabilities with an approach to address the issue of gender exclusion. This will be a continuation of an existing project which has received Scottish Government funding since 2010.</description>
